# Frontend Standards

## HTML
- Semantic HTML5 elements.
- Single `<h1>` per page.
- All interactive elements need unique, descriptive IDs.

## CSS
- CSS custom properties (variables) for theming.
- Dark theme, glassmorphism, smooth gradients.
- Micro-animations for interactions.
- Responsive: panels stack vertically on narrow viewports.
- No frameworks — vanilla CSS only.

## JavaScript
- ES modules (`type="module"` in script tags).
- `fetch()` for API calls.
- `EventSource` for SSE streaming.
- No build tools, no frameworks.
- JSDoc comments on all public functions.
